## Game State Management

Pass data between scenes and manage global game state effectively.

### Scene Data Passing
```typescript
// Pass data when starting a scene
this.scene.start('GameOverScene', { score: this.score, level: this.level });

// Receive in target scene
init(data: { score: number; level: number }) {
  this.finalScore = data.score;
  this.currentLevel = data.level;
}
```

### Global Registry (persistent across scenes)
```typescript
// Set data accessible to all scenes
this.registry.set('highScore', 9999);
this.registry.set('playerLives', 3);

// Read from any scene
const lives = this.registry.get('playerLives');

// Listen for changes
this.registry.events.on('changedata-playerLives', (parent, value) => {
  this.livesText.setText('Lives: ' + value);
});
```

### Event-Based Communication
```typescript
// GameScene emits
this.events.emit('scoreChanged', this.score);

// HUDScene listens (get reference to other scene)
const gameScene = this.scene.get('GameScene');
gameScene.events.on('scoreChanged', (score: number) => {
  this.scoreText.setText('Score: ' + score);
});
```

### Save Pattern
```typescript
const saveData = { level: 3, score: 1500, inventory: [...] };
localStorage.setItem('gameSave', JSON.stringify(saveData));
```

## Object Pooling Pattern

Reuse game objects instead of create/destroy to avoid GC spikes and improve performance.

### When to Use
- Bullets fired rapidly (shooters)
- Obstacles/coins in endless runners
- Particle-like effects (explosions)
- Any object created/destroyed frequently (>10/sec)

### Pool Setup
```typescript
// Create pool with max size
this.bulletPool = this.physics.add.group({
  classType: Phaser.Physics.Arcade.Sprite,
  maxSize: 30,
  runChildUpdate: true,
  createCallback: (obj) => {
    const bullet = obj as Phaser.Physics.Arcade.Sprite;
    bullet.setActive(false).setVisible(false);
  }
});
```

### Spawn (Get from pool)
```typescript
function spawnBullet(x: number, y: number, velocityY: number) {
  const bullet = this.bulletPool.getFirst(false, true, x, y, 'bullet');
  if (bullet) {
    bullet.setActive(true).setVisible(true);
    bullet.body!.reset(x, y);
    bullet.body!.setVelocityY(velocityY);
  }
}
```

### Recycle (Return to pool)
```typescript
// In update() or collision callback
function recycleBullet(bullet: Phaser.Physics.Arcade.Sprite) {
  bullet.setActive(false).setVisible(false);
  bullet.body!.stop();
  bullet.body!.reset(0, 0);
}
```

### Performance: Pool of 30 bullets vs creating new = ~60% less GC pressure in rapid-fire games.

## Physics System Architecture

### Choosing Physics Engine
- **Arcade Physics**: Fast, AABB-based. Use for: platformers, shooters, most 2D games. No rotation physics.
- **Matter.js**: Full rigid body. Use for: physics puzzles, complex shapes, joints, stacking. Higher CPU cost.

### Game Config
```typescript
const config: Phaser.Types.Core.GameConfig = {
  physics: {
    default: 'arcade',
    arcade: {
      gravity: { x: 0, y: 300 }, // platformer
      // gravity: { x: 0, y: 0 }, // top-down or space
      debug: false
    }
  }
};
```

### Gravity Presets by Game Type
- Platformer: `{ y: 300-600 }` (heavier = snappier jumps)
- Space shooter: `{ y: 0 }` (no gravity)
- Top-down RPG: `{ y: 0 }` (no gravity)
- Endless runner: `{ y: 800-1200 }` (fast fall for challenge)

### Collision Setup
```typescript
// Simple collision
this.physics.add.collider(player, platforms);

// Overlap with callback (collectibles)
this.physics.add.overlap(player, coins, collectCoin, undefined, this);

// World bounds
player.body!.setCollideWorldBounds(true);
this.physics.world.setBounds(0, 0, mapWidth, mapHeight);
```

### Custom Hitbox
```typescript
player.body!.setSize(24, 32); // smaller than sprite
player.body!.setOffset(4, 0); // align hitbox
```

## Responsive Game Design

Make games work across desktop and mobile with different screen sizes.

### Scale Manager Config
```typescript
const config: Phaser.Types.Core.GameConfig = {
  scale: {
    mode: Phaser.Scale.FIT, // maintain aspect ratio
    autoCenter: Phaser.Scale.CENTER_BOTH,
    width: 800,
    height: 600,
    min: { width: 400, height: 300 },
    max: { width: 1600, height: 1200 }
  }
};
```

### Scale Modes
- `FIT` — scales to fit, keeps aspect ratio (black bars possible)
- `RESIZE` — canvas matches container, game dimensions change
- `ENVELOP` — fills container, may crop edges

### Percentage-Based UI Positioning
```typescript
const { width, height } = this.scale;

// Center
this.add.text(width * 0.5, height * 0.5, 'PAUSED', style).setOrigin(0.5);

// Top-right corner (score)
this.add.text(width * 0.95, height * 0.05, 'Score: 0', style).setOrigin(1, 0);

// Bottom-center (controls hint)
this.add.text(width * 0.5, height * 0.95, 'TAP TO JUMP', style).setOrigin(0.5, 1);
```

### Mobile Detection
```typescript
if (this.sys.game.device.os.android || this.sys.game.device.os.iOS) {
  this.createTouchControls();
} else {
  this.createKeyboardControls();
}
```

### Handle Resize Events
```typescript
this.scale.on('resize', (gameSize: Phaser.Structs.Size) => {
  this.cameras.main.setViewport(0, 0, gameSize.width, gameSize.height);
});
```

## Modular Enemy System

Design enemies with configurable behaviors for easy variation and extension.

### Enemy Config Pattern
```typescript
interface EnemyConfig {
  key: string;
  hp: number;
  speed: number;
  behavior: 'patrol' | 'chase' | 'flee' | 'stationary';
  patrolRange?: number;
  detectRange?: number;
  attackDamage: number;
}

const ENEMIES: Record<string, EnemyConfig> = {
  slime: { key: 'slime', hp: 2, speed: 50, behavior: 'patrol', patrolRange: 100, detectRange: 0, attackDamage: 1 },
  bat: { key: 'bat', hp: 1, speed: 120, behavior: 'chase', detectRange: 200, attackDamage: 1 },
  boss: { key: 'boss', hp: 20, speed: 80, behavior: 'chase', detectRange: 300, attackDamage: 3 }
};
```

### Behavior in Update
```typescript
function updateEnemy(enemy: EnemySprite, player: Phaser.Physics.Arcade.Sprite) {
  const cfg = enemy.getData('config') as EnemyConfig;
  const dist = Phaser.Math.Distance.Between(enemy.x, enemy.y, player.x, player.y);

  switch (cfg.behavior) {
    case 'patrol':
      // Move back and forth within patrolRange
      if (Math.abs(enemy.x - enemy.getData('startX')) > cfg.patrolRange!) {
        enemy.body!.velocity.x *= -1;
        enemy.flipX = !enemy.flipX;
      }
      break;
    case 'chase':
      if (dist < cfg.detectRange!) {
        this.physics.moveToObject(enemy, player, cfg.speed);
      } else {
        enemy.body!.setVelocity(0);
      }
      break;
    case 'flee':
      if (dist < cfg.detectRange!) {
        const angle = Phaser.Math.Angle.Between(player.x, player.y, enemy.x, enemy.y);
        enemy.body!.setVelocity(Math.cos(angle) * cfg.speed, Math.sin(angle) * cfg.speed);
      }
      break;
  }
}
```

### Spawn Management
```typescript
this.enemyGroup = this.physics.add.group({ maxSize: 20 });

function spawnEnemy(x: number, y: number, type: string) {
  const cfg = ENEMIES[type];
  const enemy = this.enemyGroup.getFirst(false, true, x, y, cfg.key);
  if (enemy) {
    enemy.setActive(true).setVisible(true).setData('config', cfg).setData('startX', x);
    enemy.body!.setVelocityX(cfg.speed);
  }
}
```

## Tilemap Workflow

Use Tiled editor exports for level design, then load and configure in Phaser.

### Asset Loading
```typescript
preload() {
  this.load.tilemapTiledJSON('level1', 'assets/maps/level1.json');
  this.load.image('tiles', 'assets/tilesets/terrain.png');
}
```

### Create Map & Layers
```typescript
create() {
  const map = this.make.tilemap({ key: 'level1' });
  const tileset = map.addTilesetImage('terrain', 'tiles');

  // Background layer (no collision)
  const bgLayer = map.createLayer('Background', tileset!, 0, 0);

  // Ground layer (with collision)
  const groundLayer = map.createLayer('Ground', tileset!, 0, 0);
  groundLayer!.setCollisionByProperty({ collides: true });

  // Collision with player
  this.physics.add.collider(this.player, groundLayer!);

  // Set world bounds to map size
  this.physics.world.setBounds(0, 0, map.widthInPixels, map.heightInPixels);
  this.cameras.main.setBounds(0, 0, map.widthInPixels, map.heightInPixels);
}
```

### Object Layers for Spawn Points
```typescript
// In Tiled: create Object Layer 'Spawns' with point objects
const spawns = map.getObjectLayer('Spawns')!;
spawns.objects.forEach(obj => {
  if (obj.name === 'player') {
    this.player.setPosition(obj.x!, obj.y!);
  } else if (obj.name === 'enemy') {
    this.spawnEnemy(obj.x!, obj.y!, obj.type || 'slime');
  } else if (obj.name === 'coin') {
    this.coins.create(obj.x!, obj.y!, 'coin');
  }
});
```

### Collision by Tile Index (alternative)
```typescript
groundLayer!.setCollisionBetween(1, 50); // tile indices 1-50 are solid
```

## Animation Management

Organize and play animations effectively with clear naming and state logic.

### Loading Spritesheets
```typescript
preload() {
  this.load.spritesheet('player', 'assets/player.png', {
    frameWidth: 32, frameHeight: 48
  });
}
```

### Creating Animations (in create())
```typescript
// Naming convention: {entity}-{action}
this.anims.create({ key: 'player-idle', frames: this.anims.generateFrameNumbers('player', { start: 0, end: 3 }), frameRate: 6, repeat: -1 });
this.anims.create({ key: 'player-run', frames: this.anims.generateFrameNumbers('player', { start: 4, end: 9 }), frameRate: 10, repeat: -1 });
this.anims.create({ key: 'player-jump', frames: this.anims.generateFrameNumbers('player', { start: 10, end: 12 }), frameRate: 8, repeat: 0 });
this.anims.create({ key: 'player-hurt', frames: this.anims.generateFrameNumbers('player', { start: 13, end: 14 }), frameRate: 8, repeat: 0 });
```

### State-Based Animation Switching (in update())
```typescript
if (this.isHurt) {
  player.anims.play('player-hurt', true);
} else if (!player.body!.touching.down) {
  player.anims.play('player-jump', true);
} else if (Math.abs(player.body!.velocity.x) > 10) {
  player.anims.play('player-run', true);
  player.flipX = player.body!.velocity.x < 0;
} else {
  player.anims.play('player-idle', true);
}
```

### Animation Events
```typescript
player.on('animationcomplete-player-hurt', () => {
  this.isHurt = false;
});
```

### Global vs Scene Anims
Animations created with `this.anims.create()` are global (shared across scenes). Only create once, typically in a Boot/Preload scene.

## Audio System Design

Manage background music, SFX, and volume controls properly.

### Loading Audio
```typescript
preload() {
  this.load.audio('bgm', 'assets/audio/background.mp3');
  this.load.audio('jump', 'assets/audio/jump.wav');
  this.load.audio('coin', 'assets/audio/coin.wav');
  this.load.audio('hit', 'assets/audio/hit.wav');
  this.load.audio('gameover', 'assets/audio/gameover.mp3');
}
```

### Music Management
```typescript
create() {
  this.bgm = this.sound.add('bgm', { loop: true, volume: 0.4 });
  this.bgm.play();
}

// Stop on scene change
shutdown() {
  this.bgm.stop();
}
```

### SFX Pattern
```typescript
// Play one-shot sounds
this.sound.play('jump', { volume: 0.6 });
this.sound.play('coin', { volume: 0.5 });
```

### Volume & Mute Controls
```typescript
// Global mute toggle
let isMuted = false;
function toggleMute(scene: Phaser.Scene) {
  isMuted = !isMuted;
  scene.sound.mute = isMuted;
}

// Volume slider
scene.sound.volume = 0.7; // 0 to 1
```

### Mobile Audio Unlock
Browsers require user interaction before playing audio. Phaser handles this automatically if you use `scene.sound`, but ensure your first audio plays after a user tap/click event.

```typescript
// If needed manually:
this.input.once('pointerdown', () => {
  this.sound.unlock();
});
```

## Camera System Design

Set up cameras for smooth following, zooming, and multi-camera setups.

### Follow Player with Lerp
```typescript
this.cameras.main.startFollow(player, true, 0.08, 0.08);
this.cameras.main.setFollowOffset(0, -50); // look ahead vertically
```

### Dead Zone (player can move without camera moving)
```typescript
this.cameras.main.setDeadzone(200, 100);
// Camera only moves when player exits the 200x100 center area
```

### Camera Bounds (prevent showing beyond map)
```typescript
this.cameras.main.setBounds(0, 0, mapWidth, mapHeight);
```

### Zoom Effect
```typescript
// Zoom in for boss fight
this.cameras.main.zoomTo(1.5, 1000); // zoom to 1.5x over 1 second

// Zoom out for map overview
this.cameras.main.zoomTo(0.5, 500);
```

### Camera Shake (hit feedback)
```typescript
this.cameras.main.shake(200, 0.01); // duration, intensity
```

### Camera Flash/Fade
```typescript
// Death flash
this.cameras.main.flash(300, 255, 0, 0); // red flash

// Scene transition fade
this.cameras.main.fadeOut(500);
this.cameras.main.once('camerafadeoutcomplete', () => {
  this.scene.start('NextScene');
});
```

### HUD as Separate Camera/Scene
Best practice: use a separate HUDScene launched in parallel. Alternatively, set UI elements to `setScrollFactor(0)` so they stay fixed on screen:
```typescript
this.scoreText = this.add.text(16, 16, 'Score: 0', style).setScrollFactor(0).setDepth(1000);
```

## Input Abstraction Layer

Unify keyboard, touch, and gamepad input into a single interface.

### Input State Interface
```typescript
interface InputState {
  left: boolean;
  right: boolean;
  up: boolean;
  down: boolean;
  jump: boolean;
  fire: boolean;
}
```

### Keyboard Input
```typescript
const cursors = this.input.keyboard!.createCursorKeys();
const wasd = this.input.keyboard!.addKeys('W,A,S,D') as any;
const space = this.input.keyboard!.addKey('SPACE');

function getKeyboardInput(): InputState {
  return {
    left: cursors.left.isDown || wasd.A.isDown,
    right: cursors.right.isDown || wasd.D.isDown,
    up: cursors.up.isDown || wasd.W.isDown,
    down: cursors.down.isDown || wasd.S.isDown,
    jump: Phaser.Input.Keyboard.JustDown(space),
    fire: Phaser.Input.Keyboard.JustDown(cursors.shift)
  };
}
```

### Virtual Joystick for Mobile
```typescript
// Simple touch zones approach
const leftZone = this.add.zone(100, height - 100, 200, 200).setInteractive();
const rightZone = this.add.zone(width - 100, height - 100, 150, 150).setInteractive();

let touchLeft = false, touchRight = false, touchJump = false;
leftZone.on('pointerdown', () => { touchLeft = true; });
leftZone.on('pointerup', () => { touchLeft = false; });
rightZone.on('pointerdown', () => { touchJump = true; });
rightZone.on('pointerup', () => { touchJump = false; });
```

### Unified Read in update()
```typescript
update() {
  const input = getKeyboardInput();
  // Merge touch
  input.left = input.left || touchLeft;
  input.jump = input.jump || touchJump;

  // Apply to player
  if (input.left) player.body!.setVelocityX(-200);
  else if (input.right) player.body!.setVelocityX(200);
  else player.body!.setVelocityX(0);
  if (input.jump && player.body!.touching.down) player.body!.setVelocityY(-400);
}
```

## Particle Effect Cookbook

Common particle configurations for visual feedback and atmosphere.

### Explosion Effect
```typescript
function createExplosion(scene: Phaser.Scene, x: number, y: number) {
  const particles = scene.add.particles(x, y, 'particle', {
    speed: { min: 100, max: 300 },
    angle: { min: 0, max: 360 },
    scale: { start: 1, end: 0 },
    lifespan: 500,
    quantity: 20,
    emitting: false
  });
  particles.explode(20);
  scene.time.delayedCall(600, () => particles.destroy());
}
```

### Coin Collect Sparkle
```typescript
const sparkle = scene.add.particles(x, y, 'spark', {
  speed: { min: 50, max: 150 },
  scale: { start: 0.5, end: 0 },
  lifespan: 300,
  tint: [0xffff00, 0xffd700],
  quantity: 8,
  emitting: false
});
sparkle.explode(8);
```

### Trail Effect (following player)
```typescript
const trail = scene.add.particles(0, 0, 'particle', {
  speed: 20,
  scale: { start: 0.3, end: 0 },
  alpha: { start: 0.6, end: 0 },
  lifespan: 400,
  frequency: 50,
  follow: player
});
```

### Rain Effect
```typescript
scene.add.particles(0, -10, 'raindrop', {
  x: { min: 0, max: scene.scale.width },
  speedY: { min: 300, max: 500 },
  speedX: { min: -50, max: -20 },
  scale: { min: 0.2, max: 0.5 },
  lifespan: 2000,
  frequency: 20,
  quantity: 2
});
```

### Performance: Always set `maxParticles` or destroy emitters after burst effects. Never leave unlimited emitters running.

## Performance Optimization

Keep your game running at stable 60fps with these techniques.

### 1. Use Object Pools
Never `new` + `destroy()` in rapid succession. Use Groups with maxSize (see arch-object-pooling).

### 2. Texture Atlas over Individual Images
```typescript
// BAD: 50 separate image loads
this.load.image('enemy1', ...);
this.load.image('enemy2', ...);

// GOOD: Single atlas with all sprites
this.load.atlas('sprites', 'assets/sprites.png', 'assets/sprites.json');
this.add.sprite(100, 100, 'sprites', 'enemy1');
```
One draw call for atlas vs one per texture. Major GPU improvement.

### 3. Minimize update() Work
```typescript
// BAD: Distance check every frame for all enemies
update() {
  this.enemies.forEach(e => checkDistance(e)); // 100 enemies = 100 checks/frame
}

// GOOD: Throttle expensive checks
this.time.addEvent({
  delay: 200, // check 5x per second, not 60x
  loop: true,
  callback: () => this.updateEnemyAI()
});
```

### 4. Offscreen Culling
```typescript
// Disable physics for offscreen objects
this.enemies.getChildren().forEach(e => {
  const sprite = e as Phaser.Physics.Arcade.Sprite;
  const onScreen = this.cameras.main.worldView.contains(sprite.x, sprite.y);
  sprite.body!.enable = onScreen;
});
```

### 5. Cleanup on Scene Stop
```typescript
shutdown() {
  this.events.off('update');
  this.time.removeAllEvents();
  // Groups auto-cleanup, but custom references need clearing
}
```

### 6. Use `setVisible(false)` + `setActive(false)` instead of destroy() when objects will be reused.

## Debug Techniques

Tools and patterns for diagnosing game issues during development.

### Physics Debug Visualization
```typescript
const config = {
  physics: {
    arcade: {
      debug: true, // shows hitboxes, velocity vectors
      debugShowBody: true,
      debugShowStaticBody: true,
      debugBodyColor: 0xff00ff
    }
  }
};
```

### FPS Monitor
```typescript
create() {
  this.fpsText = this.add.text(10, 10, '', { fontSize: '14px', color: '#0f0' })
    .setScrollFactor(0).setDepth(9999);
}
update() {
  this.fpsText.setText('FPS: ' + Math.round(this.game.loop.actualFps));
}
```

### Console Logging Patterns
```typescript
// Log once on event, not every frame
this.physics.add.overlap(player, zone, () => {
  console.log('Player entered zone at', player.x, player.y);
}, undefined, this);

// Debug flag to toggle verbose logging
const DEBUG = true;
if (DEBUG) console.log('Enemy spawned:', config);
```

### Scene Inspection
```typescript
// List all game objects in scene
console.log('Objects:', this.children.list.length);
console.log('Physics bodies:', this.physics.world.bodies.size);

// Check specific group
console.log('Active bullets:', this.bullets.countActive(true));
console.log('Inactive bullets:', this.bullets.countActive(false));
```

### Common Issues Checklist
1. Object not visible? Check: depth, alpha, position, camera bounds
2. Collision not working? Check: body enabled, overlap vs collider, correct groups
3. Animation not playing? Check: key exists, spritesheet loaded, frameRate > 0
4. Sounds not playing? Check: user interaction occurred, audio context unlocked

## UI System Design

Build menus, HUDs, buttons, and responsive UI overlays in Phaser.

### Interactive Button
```typescript
function createButton(scene: Phaser.Scene, x: number, y: number, text: string, onClick: () => void) {
  const btn = scene.add.text(x, y, text, {
    fontSize: '24px', color: '#fff', backgroundColor: '#333',
    padding: { x: 20, y: 10 }
  }).setOrigin(0.5).setInteractive({ useHandCursor: true });

  btn.on('pointerover', () => btn.setStyle({ color: '#ff0' }));
  btn.on('pointerout', () => btn.setStyle({ color: '#fff' }));
  btn.on('pointerdown', onClick);
  return btn;
}
```

### Menu Layout
```typescript
create() {
  const { width, height } = this.scale;
  this.add.text(width / 2, height * 0.2, 'GAME TITLE', {
    fontSize: '48px', color: '#fff', fontFamily: 'Arial'
  }).setOrigin(0.5);

  createButton(this, width / 2, height * 0.5, 'START GAME', () => this.scene.start('GameScene'));
  createButton(this, width / 2, height * 0.6, 'SETTINGS', () => this.scene.launch('SettingsScene'));
  createButton(this, width / 2, height * 0.7, 'CREDITS', () => this.scene.start('CreditsScene'));
}
```

### Health Bar
```typescript
function createHealthBar(scene: Phaser.Scene, x: number, y: number, width: number, height: number) {
  const bg = scene.add.rectangle(x, y, width, height, 0x333333).setOrigin(0, 0.5);
  const bar = scene.add.rectangle(x, y, width, height, 0x00ff00).setOrigin(0, 0.5);

  return {
    update(percent: number) {
      bar.width = width * Phaser.Math.Clamp(percent, 0, 1);
      bar.fillColor = percent > 0.5 ? 0x00ff00 : percent > 0.25 ? 0xffff00 : 0xff0000;
    }
  };
}

// Usage
const hpBar = createHealthBar(this, 16, 16, 200, 20);
hpBar.update(player.hp / player.maxHp);
```

### Score Display (fixed to camera)
```typescript
this.scoreText = this.add.text(16, 16, 'Score: 0', {
  fontSize: '20px', color: '#fff'
}).setScrollFactor(0).setDepth(100);
```

### Responsive Text Sizing
```typescript
const fontSize = Math.max(16, Math.floor(this.scale.width / 30));
```
